commit.message:
8373288: EnumMap spliterators should include more specific characteristics

The spliterators returned by keySet, entrySet, and values were not reporting additional
characteristics, such as ORDERED, SORTED, and NONNULL; the EnumMap iterators all guarantee
iteration is in the natural order of the enum key, and nulls are disallowed as keys.

Null values are allowed, so the values collection can only additionally report ORDERED.
